main event: About 20 white-yellow lights were observed in Cincinnati, Ohio for 25 minutes on July 29, 1966.
interesting points: The lights appeared to be rotating but were determined to be an aircraft with extraneous lights., The lights flickered and blinked during the observation., The observer estimated the object to be moving at a speed of 35-60 MPH., The object was described as brighter than a street light and solid., The observer noted no sound and described the object's color as white-yellowish.
sighted object: about 20 flickering white-yellow lights in the sky
witness description: A civilian observer who reported the sighting.
